cs.CC, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.CG 

The paper deals with the complexity of two connection games, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of reduction from Generalized Geography and ring-threats to represent the input graph suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The study of connection games also involves graph theory, which is covered under the sub-categories of game theory (cs.GT) and computational geometry (cs.CG).
